description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;WORCESTERSHIRE PERINATAL PSYCHIATRY TEAM – STUDDERT KENNEDY HOUSE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Occupational Therapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5hrs per week – Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We wish to recruit a 12 month fixed term, Band 6 Occupational Therapist to work as part of the multi-disciplinary clinical team; providing specialist Occupational Therapy Interventions and treatment via individual and group work programmes for our countywide perinatal service patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Worcestershire Perinatal Psychiatry Team is accredited by the Royal College of Psychiatrists; we are a busy, secondary care mental health service that offers a range of NICE concordant mental health interventions to the women of Worcestershire. The team is small and we operate on a Recovery based, ‘patient first’ service ethos.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Professional development is encouraged. There are strong links with local and regional Occupational Therapy CPD and training networks including regular trainees on specialist placements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers a fantastic opportunity to gain experience working in a multi-disciplinary team of highly-skilled and knowledgeable clinicians.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will ideally be able to demonstrate experience of working in a perinatal field, or alternatively will be able to demonstrate in interview a thorough understanding of the specific role an OT will fulfil in a perinatal service pathway. The candidate will have access to funding to enable perinatal specialist training to be completed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be based at Studdert Kennedy House in Worcester, however must be able to work across this large rural county as the service needs require. The service operates from 9am-5pm, Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, or informal discussion, please contact any of the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Catherine Cale, Clinical Lead, Perinatal Psychiatry Team or Sian Westaway, Service Lead for Adult Mental Health Specialist teams - 01905 734531&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
